This paper employed CCEP mapping with single pulse electrical stimulation and ECoG arrays in 25 human subjects. Adjacent electrode pairs were stimulated, and CCEPs were recorded from the other electrodes. The discovered connections between regions were often bidirectional. Motor cortex, Ba6-BA9, somatosensory cortex, anterior cingulate cortex, and Broca's were the most consistent outward connections. Motor, somatosensory cortex, anterior cingulate cortex, BA9 and BA10 and language areas served as cortical connection hubs. BA20 and BA30 showed most consistently dominance of outward connections. BA5, BA7, auditory cortex, and anterior cingulam showed more indegree of connections.},
